# CAD & Digital Modeling Portfolio

This repository demonstrates basic workflows used in computer-aided design (CAD) and digital modeling environments.

The examples focus on fundamental concepts used in engineering design, architectural modeling, and digital asset creation.

## Skills Demonstrated

• 2D drafting concepts  
• 3D parametric modeling  
• CAD design workflows  
• digital asset modeling  
• BIM data structure concepts  

## Example Projects

### Mechanical Component Modeling
Basic 3D modeling of mechanical parts using parametric design concepts.

### Architectural Layout Drafting
2D drafting workflows for architectural floor plans and layouts.

### BIM Data Structure Concepts
Examples of building information modeling workflows and IFC data structure organization.

## Tools Referenced

FreeCAD  
AutoCAD Mechanical  
Rhino 3D  
Vectorworks  
BlenderBIM  

## Purpose

This repository demonstrates knowledge of CAD and digital modeling workflows relevant to engineering design and AI training applications.
